    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 286</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Adviser to the United
                        States Delegation</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_YKT1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract]</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1954-05-25">May 25, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Questions Relating to Southeast Asia and Korea</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>Participants:</head>
                    <item>Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName>, Thailand
                        Delegation</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, U.S.
                        Delegation</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YKT1">Kenneth T. Young</persName>, Jr., U.S.
                        Delegation</item>
                </list>
                <p>Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> informed Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> that the Government of Thailand had
                    decided to proceed with an appeal to the United Nations regarding aggression in
                    Cambodia and Laos and had instructed its representative in New York to discuss
                    the Thai communication to the United Nations with Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> before filing it. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> expressed his gratification that the
                    Thai Government had taken this action and hoped that it would be carried out as
                    quickly as possible. Prince <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> also
                    informed Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>, who agreed, that
                    it would be better to hold off discussion on certain military matters until
                    Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_PS2">Sarasin</persName> had returned to Geneva,
                    which now would be <pb facs="0946" n="920" xml:id="pg_920"/> Saturday.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d599fn1">May 29.</note> He explained that Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_PS2">Sarasin</persName> would have the benefit of the views of
                    the Prime Minister.</p>
                <p>. . . . . . .</p>
